\title{Refuse Mediocrity}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{trit}{+1}

\meta{description}{"Reject complacency. Demand excellence. Ship or die."}

\subtree{
\title{Refuse Mediocrity}
\p{\strong{Trit}: +1 (GENERATOR - creates pressure toward excellence)}

\subtree{
\title{Core Principle}
\p{Mediocrity is the enemy. Not failure—failure teaches. Mediocrity is the comfortable middle that produces nothing memorable, changes nothing, matters to no one.}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Standard}
\pre{\startverb
REFUSE:
- "Good enough"
- "We'll fix it later"
- "That's how it's always been done"
- "Nobody will notice"
- Meetings without outcomes
- Code without tests
- Ideas without execution
- Plans without deadlines

DEMAND:
- Unreasonable quality
- Obsessive attention to detail
- Speed AND excellence (not either/or)
- Shipping over perfecting
- Learning over defending
- Building over talking
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Triads}
\pre{\startverb
shadow-goblin (-1) ⊗ chromatic-walk (0) ⊗ refuse-mediocrity (+1) = 0 ✓  [Quality Trace]
three-match (-1) ⊗ unworld (0) ⊗ refuse-mediocrity (+1) = 0 ✓  [Standard Derivation]
temporal-coalgebra (-1) ⊗ kinetic-block (0) ⊗ refuse-mediocrity (+1) = 0 ✓  [Momentum]
spi-parallel-verify (-1) ⊗ implicit-coordination (0) ⊗ refuse-mediocrity (+1) = 0 ✓  [Parallel Excellence]
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Implementation}
\subtree{
\title{Before Every Commit}
\pre{\startverb
# Ask: Is this excellent?
# If hesitation → not ready
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Before Every Ship}
\pre{\startverb
# Ask: Would I be proud to show this to someone I respect?
# If no → iterate
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Before Every Meeting}
\pre{\startverb
# Ask: What decision will we make?
# If unclear → cancel
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Math}
\p{Excellence compounds. Mediocrity compounds too.}

\pre{\startverb
E(t) = E₀ × (1 + r)^t   # r > 0: excellence grows exponentially
M(t) = M₀ × (1 - d)^t   # d > 0: mediocrity decays to irrelevance
\stopverb}

\p{Choose your curve.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quotes}
\blockquote{"Be so good they can't ignore you." — Cal Newport}

\blockquote{"The only way to do great work is to love what you do." — Jobs}

\blockquote{"Move fast and break things. Unless you are breaking stuff, you are not moving fast enough." — Zuckerberg (early)}

\blockquote{"Perfectionism is the voice of the oppressor." — Lamott (But mediocrity is surrender to the oppressor.)}
}

\subtree{
\title{Anti-Patterns to Destroy}
\pre{\startverb
| Mediocrity Pattern | Excellence Response |
|-------------------|---------------------|
| "Let's circle back" | Decide now or kill it |
| "We need more data" | Ship and measure |
| "It's blocked by X" | Unblock or route around |
| "That's not my job" | Everything is your job |
| "We tried that before" | Try it better |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{The Generator Role (+1)}
\p{This skill is PLUS because it \strong{generates pressure}:}

\ul{
\li{Pressure to ship}
\li{Pressure to improve}
\li{Pressure to care}
\li{Pressure to matter}
}

\p{Without this pressure, entropy wins. Systems decay to mediocrity by default.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Usage}
\pre{\startverb
# Invoke before any significant action
just refuse-mediocrity

# Review output against excellence standard
just quality-check

# Ship only when proud
just ship-it
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{One Rule}
\p{\strong{If you wouldn't sign your name to it, don't ship it.}}
}
}